text: The 1996 Algarve Cup was the third edition of the Algarve Cup, a women's association football tournament. It took place between 11 and 17 March 1996 in Portugal. Norway won the event for the second time in its history, beating Sweden, 4-0 in the final-game. == Awards == Best player Hege Riise == References == == Other websites == * 1996 Algarve Cup on RSSSF Algarve Cup Algarve Cup Category:Algarve Cup
